Missing Pillar Pages (Identified from SEO Sheet):
Numerous /services/ pages (e.g., accounting-outsourcing, payroll-services).
Numerous /comparison/ pages (e.g., best-accounting-firms).
These missing pages were not yet created as navigable main pages.
III. Strategic Direction and Renaming (SEO & Project Lead Integration)
Pillar Page Prioritization: Build core pillar pages first.
Homepage
Main Services Hub
IT Staffing Pillar
Accounting Solutions Pillar
Call Center Outsourcing
Finance & Accounting Outsourcing
Renaming/Reconceptualizing Pages:
"IT Staffing & Development" was changed to "IT Staffing" (with URL /services/it-staffing).
"Accounting & Finance" was split into "Accounting Solutions" and "Finance & Accounting Outsourcing."
"IT Staffing" was subsequently renamed to "Nearshore IT Staffing" to align with SEO strategy.
Strategic Consolidation: Five separate low-value "hire [role]" pages were consolidated into one consolidated, authoritative IT Hub page ("Nearshore IT Staffing & Data Engineering").
IV. Site Architecture Recommendation (SEO Expert Assessment)
Service-Related Pages: Recommended to use the /services/ prefix (e.g., /services/accounting-solutions).
Audience-Specific Pages (Solutions): Recommended to use the /solutions/ prefix (e.g., /solutions/for-agencies).
Industry Pages: Recommended to use the /industries/ prefix.
V. Actionable Steps and Autonomous Work Completed
Blank Pages: To be deleted or repurposed.
Pillar Pages: Individual pillar pages for high-priority SEO pages were to be created and linked in the navigation.
Structural Improvements Completed (Autonomous Work):
CMS Collections were populated (Solutions, Services, Resources).
Dynamic Page Infrastructure for Services, Solutions, Industries, and Resources was REBUILT and functional.
Autonomous work fixed broken dataset connections and recreated corrupted/missing dynamic pages.
VI. Comprehensive Site Analysis (November 15, 2025 - Weaknesses and Gaps)
GitHub Status: Repository returned a 404 error (Access needed).
Content/CMS Gaps (Low Real Content): Only 8 total real content items across Solutions, Services, Resources, and Locations collections.
Empty/Incomplete Collections: Case Studies, Industries (minimal), People, and Roles collections were empty or incomplete.
Weaknesses Identified:
Content Gaps (Case Studies, Roles).
